<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n18128d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n18" href="#n18128d">N18 (VI.B.8)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n18all.htm#n18128d"> 128(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> handicraft</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">The municipal records of Dublin show that in 1681 the Common Council of the city authorised collections to be made in the city and Liberties for the benefit of French Protestant refugees in Dublin, in order to enable them to set up in their respective trades and callings. It was further ordered &ldquo;that all such of the said persecuted Protestants as shall within five years from the date hereof make their application for their freedoms here, and are artisans and <mark>handicraftsmen</mark>, shall be admitted to the freedom of this city without fines or fees, and also, for the space of five years to come from the date hereof, shall be freed of all city taxes.&rdquo; <small> J. J. Webb, <a name="WSID" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#WSID"><cite title="source">The Silk Industry in Ireland</cite></a> (1913) 127f</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
